4054 /// FunctionType - C99 6.7.5.3 - Function Declarators. This is the common base
4055 /// class of FunctionNoProtoType and FunctionProtoType.
4056 class FunctionType : public Type {
4057  // The type returned by the function.
4058  QualType ResultType;
4059 
4060 public:
4061  /// Interesting information about a specific parameter that can't simply
4062  /// be reflected in parameter's type. This is only used by FunctionProtoType
4063  /// but is in FunctionType to make this class available during the
4064  /// specification of the bases of FunctionProtoType.
4065  ///
4066  /// It makes sense to model language features this way when there's some
4067  /// sort of parameter-specific override (such as an attribute) that
4068  /// affects how the function is called. For example, the ARC ns_consumed
4069  /// attribute changes whether a parameter is passed at +0 (the default)
4070  /// or +1 (ns_consumed). This must be reflected in the function type,
4071  /// but isn't really a change to the parameter type.
4072  ///
4073  /// One serious disadvantage of modelling language features this way is
4074  /// that they generally do not work with language features that attempt
4075  /// to destructure types. For example, template argument deduction will
4076  /// not be able to match a parameter declared as
4077  /// T (*)(U)
4078  /// against an argument of type
4079  /// void (*)(__attribute__((ns_consumed)) id)
4080  /// because the substitution of T=void, U=id into the former will
4081  /// not produce the latter.
4082  class ExtParameterInfo {
4083  enum {
4084  ABIMask = 0x0F,
4085  IsConsumed = 0x10,
4086  HasPassObjSize = 0x20,
4087  IsNoEscape = 0x40,
4088  };
4089  unsigned char Data = 0;
4090 
4091  public:
4092  ExtParameterInfo() = default;
4093 
4094  /// Return the ABI treatment of this parameter.
4095  ParameterABI getABI() const { return ParameterABI(Data & ABIMask); }
4096  ExtParameterInfo withABI(ParameterABI kind) const {
4097  ExtParameterInfo copy = *this;
4098  copy.Data = (copy.Data & ~ABIMask) | unsigned(kind);
4099  return copy;
4100  }
4101 
4102  /// Is this parameter considered "consumed" by Objective-C ARC?
4103  /// Consumed parameters must have retainable object type.
4104  bool isConsumed() const { return (Data & IsConsumed); }
4105  ExtParameterInfo withIsConsumed(bool consumed) const {
4106  ExtParameterInfo copy = *this;
4107  if (consumed)
4108  copy.Data |= IsConsumed;
4109  else
4110  copy.Data &= ~IsConsumed;
4111  return copy;
4112  }
4113 
4114  bool hasPassObjectSize() const { return Data & HasPassObjSize; }
4115  ExtParameterInfo withHasPassObjectSize() const {
4116  ExtParameterInfo Copy = *this;
4117  Copy.Data |= HasPassObjSize;
4118  return Copy;
4119  }
4120 
4121  bool isNoEscape() const { return Data & IsNoEscape; }
4122  ExtParameterInfo withIsNoEscape(bool NoEscape) const {
4123  ExtParameterInfo Copy = *this;
4124  if (NoEscape)
4125  Copy.Data |= IsNoEscape;
4126  else
4127  Copy.Data &= ~IsNoEscape;
4128  return Copy;
4129  }
4130 
4131  unsigned char getOpaqueValue() const { return Data; }
4132  static ExtParameterInfo getFromOpaqueValue(unsigned char data) {
4133  ExtParameterInfo result;
4134  result.Data = data;
4135  return result;
4136  }
4137 
4138  friend bool operator==(ExtParameterInfo lhs, ExtParameterInfo rhs) {
4139  return lhs.Data == rhs.Data;
4140  }
4141 
4142  friend bool operator!=(ExtParameterInfo lhs, ExtParameterInfo rhs) {
4143  return lhs.Data != rhs.Data;
4144  }
4145  };
4146 
4147  /// A class which abstracts out some details necessary for
4148  /// making a call.
4149  ///
4150  /// It is not actually used directly for storing this information in
4151  /// a FunctionType, although FunctionType does currently use the
4152  /// same bit-pattern.
4153  ///
4154  // If you add a field (say Foo), other than the obvious places (both,
4155  // constructors, compile failures), what you need to update is
4156  // * Operator==
4157  // * getFoo
4158  // * withFoo
4159  // * functionType. Add Foo, getFoo.
4160  // * ASTContext::getFooType
4161  // * ASTContext::mergeFunctionTypes
4162  // * FunctionNoProtoType::Profile
4163  // * FunctionProtoType::Profile
4164  // * TypePrinter::PrintFunctionProto
4165  // * AST read and write
4166  // * Codegen
4167  class ExtInfo {
4168  friend class FunctionType;
4169 
4170  // Feel free to rearrange or add bits, but if you go over 16, you'll need to
4171  // adjust the Bits field below, and if you add bits, you'll need to adjust
4172  // Type::FunctionTypeBitfields::ExtInfo as well.
4173 
4174  // | CC |noreturn|produces|nocallersavedregs|regparm|nocfcheck|cmsenscall|
4175  // |0 .. 4| 5 | 6 | 7 |8 .. 10| 11 | 12 |
4176  //
4177  // regparm is either 0 (no regparm attribute) or the regparm value+1.
4178  enum { CallConvMask = 0x1F };
4179  enum { NoReturnMask = 0x20 };
4180  enum { ProducesResultMask = 0x40 };
4181  enum { NoCallerSavedRegsMask = 0x80 };
4182  enum {
4183  RegParmMask = 0x700,
4184  RegParmOffset = 8
4185  };
4186  enum { NoCfCheckMask = 0x800 };
4187  enum { CmseNSCallMask = 0x1000 };
4188  uint16_t Bits = CC_C;
4189 
4190  ExtInfo(unsigned Bits) : Bits(static_cast<uint16_t>(Bits)) {}
4191 
4192  public:
4193  // Constructor with no defaults. Use this when you know that you
4194  // have all the elements (when reading an AST file for example).
4195  ExtInfo(bool noReturn, bool hasRegParm, unsigned regParm, CallingConv cc,
4196  bool producesResult, bool noCallerSavedRegs, bool NoCfCheck,
4197  bool cmseNSCall) {
4198  assert((!hasRegParm || regParm < 7) && "Invalid regparm value");
4199  Bits = ((unsigned)cc) | (noReturn ? NoReturnMask : 0) |
4200  (producesResult ? ProducesResultMask : 0) |
4201  (noCallerSavedRegs ? NoCallerSavedRegsMask : 0) |
4202  (hasRegParm ? ((regParm + 1) << RegParmOffset) : 0) |
4203  (NoCfCheck ? NoCfCheckMask : 0) |
4204  (cmseNSCall ? CmseNSCallMask : 0);
4205  }
4206 
4207  // Constructor with all defaults. Use when for example creating a
4208  // function known to use defaults.
4209  ExtInfo() = default;
4210 
4211  // Constructor with just the calling convention, which is an important part
4212  // of the canonical type.
4213  ExtInfo(CallingConv CC) : Bits(CC) {}
4214 
4215  bool getNoReturn() const { return Bits & NoReturnMask; }
4216  bool getProducesResult() const { return Bits & ProducesResultMask; }
4217  bool getCmseNSCall() const { return Bits & CmseNSCallMask; }
4218  bool getNoCallerSavedRegs() const { return Bits & NoCallerSavedRegsMask; }
4219  bool getNoCfCheck() const { return Bits & NoCfCheckMask; }
4220  bool getHasRegParm() const { return ((Bits & RegParmMask) >> RegParmOffset) != 0; }
4221 
4222  unsigned getRegParm() const {
4223  unsigned RegParm = (Bits & RegParmMask) >> RegParmOffset;
4224  if (RegParm > 0)
4225  --RegParm;
4226  return RegParm;
4227  }
4228 
4229  CallingConv getCC() const { return CallingConv(Bits & CallConvMask); }
4230 
4231  bool operator==(ExtInfo Other) const {
4232  return Bits == Other.Bits;
4233  }
4234  bool operator!=(ExtInfo Other) const {
4235  return Bits != Other.Bits;
4236  }
4237 
4238  // Note that we don't have setters. That is by design, use
4239  // the following with methods instead of mutating these objects.
4240 
4241  ExtInfo withNoReturn(bool noReturn) const {
4242  if (noReturn)
4243  return ExtInfo(Bits | NoReturnMask);
4244  else
4245  return ExtInfo(Bits & ~NoReturnMask);
4246  }
4247 
4248  ExtInfo withProducesResult(bool producesResult) const {
4249  if (producesResult)
4250  return ExtInfo(Bits | ProducesResultMask);
4251  else
4252  return ExtInfo(Bits & ~ProducesResultMask);
4253  }
4254 
4255  ExtInfo withCmseNSCall(bool cmseNSCall) const {
4256  if (cmseNSCall)
4257  return ExtInfo(Bits | CmseNSCallMask);
4258  else
4259  return ExtInfo(Bits & ~CmseNSCallMask);
4260  }
4261 
4262  ExtInfo withNoCallerSavedRegs(bool noCallerSavedRegs) const {
4263  if (noCallerSavedRegs)
4264  return ExtInfo(Bits | NoCallerSavedRegsMask);
4265  else
4266  return ExtInfo(Bits & ~NoCallerSavedRegsMask);
4267  }
4268 
4269  ExtInfo withNoCfCheck(bool noCfCheck) const {
4270  if (noCfCheck)
4271  return ExtInfo(Bits | NoCfCheckMask);
4272  else
4273  return ExtInfo(Bits & ~NoCfCheckMask);
4274  }
4275 
4276  ExtInfo withRegParm(unsigned RegParm) const {
4277  assert(RegParm < 7 && "Invalid regparm value");
4278  return ExtInfo((Bits & ~RegParmMask) |
4279  ((RegParm + 1) << RegParmOffset));
4280  }
4281 
4282  ExtInfo withCallingConv(CallingConv cc) const {
4283  return ExtInfo((Bits & ~CallConvMask) | (unsigned) cc);
4284  }
4285 
4286  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) const {
4287  ID.AddInteger(Bits);
4288  }
4289  };

4291  /// A simple holder for a QualType representing a type in an
4292  /// exception specification. Unfortunately needed by FunctionProtoType
4293  /// because TrailingObjects cannot handle repeated types.
4294  struct ExceptionType { QualType Type; };
4295 
4296  /// A simple holder for various uncommon bits which do not fit in
4297  /// FunctionTypeBitfields. Aligned to alignof(void *) to maintain the
4298  /// alignment of subsequent objects in TrailingObjects.
4299  struct alignas(void *) FunctionTypeExtraBitfields {
4300  /// The number of types in the exception specification.
4301  /// A whole unsigned is not needed here and according to
4302  /// [implimits] 8 bits would be enough here.
4303  unsigned NumExceptionType : 10;
4304 
4305  LLVM_PREFERRED_TYPE(bool)
4306  unsigned HasArmTypeAttributes : 1;
4307 
4308  FunctionTypeExtraBitfields()
4309  : NumExceptionType(0), HasArmTypeAttributes(false) {}
4310  };
4311 
4312  /// The AArch64 SME ACLE (Arm C/C++ Language Extensions) define a number
4313  /// of function type attributes that can be set on function types, including
4314  /// function pointers.
4315  enum AArch64SMETypeAttributes : unsigned {
4316  SME_NormalFunction = 0,
4317  SME_PStateSMEnabledMask = 1 << 0,
4318  SME_PStateSMCompatibleMask = 1 << 1,
4319 
4320  // Describes the value of the state using ArmStateValue.
4321  SME_ZAShift = 2,
4322  SME_ZAMask = 0b111 << SME_ZAShift,
4323  SME_ZT0Shift = 5,
4324  SME_ZT0Mask = 0b111 << SME_ZT0Shift,
4325 
4326  SME_AttributeMask =
4327  0b111'111'11 // We can't support more than 8 bits because of
4328  // the bitmask in FunctionTypeExtraBitfields.
4329  };
4330 
4331  enum ArmStateValue : unsigned {
4332  ARM_None = 0,
4333  ARM_Preserves = 1,
4334  ARM_In = 2,
4335  ARM_Out = 3,
4336  ARM_InOut = 4,
4337  };
4338 
4339  static ArmStateValue getArmZAState(unsigned AttrBits) {
4340  return (ArmStateValue)((AttrBits & SME_ZAMask) >> SME_ZAShift);
4341  }
4342 
4343  static ArmStateValue getArmZT0State(unsigned AttrBits) {
4344  return (ArmStateValue)((AttrBits & SME_ZT0Mask) >> SME_ZT0Shift);
4345  }

4351  /// Any AArch64 SME ACLE type attributes that need to be propagated
4352  /// on declarations and function pointers.
4353  unsigned AArch64SMEAttributes : 8;
4354

4356  };

4442 /// Represents a prototype with parameter type info, e.g.
4443 /// 'int foo(int)' or 'int foo(void)'. 'void' is represented as having no
4444 /// parameters, not as having a single void parameter. Such a type can have
4445 /// an exception specification, but this specification is not part of the
4446 /// canonical type. FunctionProtoType has several trailing objects, some of
4447 /// which optional. For more information about the trailing objects see
4448 /// the first comment inside FunctionProtoType.
4449 class FunctionProtoType final
4450  : public FunctionType,
4451  public llvm::FoldingSetNode,
4452  private llvm::TrailingObjects<
4453  FunctionProtoType, QualType, SourceLocation,
4454  FunctionType::FunctionTypeExtraBitfields,
4455  FunctionType::FunctionTypeArmAttributes, FunctionType::ExceptionType,
4456  Expr *, FunctionDecl *, FunctionType::ExtParameterInfo, Qualifiers> {
4457  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these.
4458  friend TrailingObjects;
4459 
4460  // FunctionProtoType is followed by several trailing objects, some of
4461  // which optional. They are in order:
4462  //
4463  // * An array of getNumParams() QualType holding the parameter types.
4464  // Always present. Note that for the vast majority of FunctionProtoType,
4465  // these will be the only trailing objects.
4466  //
4467  // * Optionally if the function is variadic, the SourceLocation of the
4468  // ellipsis.
4469  //
4470  // * Optionally if some extra data is stored in FunctionTypeExtraBitfields
4471  // (see FunctionTypeExtraBitfields and FunctionTypeBitfields):
4472  // a single FunctionTypeExtraBitfields. Present if and only if
4473  // hasExtraBitfields() is true.
4474  //
4475  // * Optionally exactly one of:
4476  // * an array of getNumExceptions() ExceptionType,
4477  // * a single Expr *,
4478  // * a pair of FunctionDecl *,
4479  // * a single FunctionDecl *
4480  // used to store information about the various types of exception
4481  // specification. See getExceptionSpecSize for the details.
4482  //
4483  // * Optionally an array of getNumParams() ExtParameterInfo holding
4484  // an ExtParameterInfo for each of the parameters. Present if and
4485  // only if hasExtParameterInfos() is true.
4486  //
4487  // * Optionally a Qualifiers object to represent extra qualifiers that can't
4488  // be represented by FunctionTypeBitfields.FastTypeQuals. Present if and only
4489  // if hasExtQualifiers() is true.
4490  //
4491  // The optional FunctionTypeExtraBitfields has to be before the data
4492  // related to the exception specification since it contains the number
4493  // of exception types.
4494  //
4495  // We put the ExtParameterInfos last. If all were equal, it would make
4496  // more sense to put these before the exception specification, because
4497  // it's much easier to skip past them compared to the elaborate switch
4498  // required to skip the exception specification. However, all is not
4499  // equal; ExtParameterInfos are used to model very uncommon features,
4500  // and it's better not to burden the more common paths.
4501 
4502 public:
4503  /// Holds information about the various types of exception specification.
4504  /// ExceptionSpecInfo is not stored as such in FunctionProtoType but is
4505  /// used to group together the various bits of information about the
4506  /// exception specification.
4507  struct ExceptionSpecInfo {
4508  /// The kind of exception specification this is.
4509  ExceptionSpecificationType Type = EST_None;
4510 
4511  /// Explicitly-specified list of exception types.
4512  ArrayRef<QualType> Exceptions;
4513 
4514  /// Noexcept expression, if this is a computed noexcept specification.
4515  Expr *NoexceptExpr = nullptr;
4516 
4517  /// The function whose exception specification this is, for
4518  /// EST_Unevaluated and EST_Uninstantiated.
4519  FunctionDecl *SourceDecl = nullptr;
4520 
4521  /// The function template whose exception specification this is instantiated
4522  /// from, for EST_Uninstantiated.
4523  FunctionDecl *SourceTemplate = nullptr;
4524 
4525  ExceptionSpecInfo() = default;
4526 
4527  ExceptionSpecInfo(ExceptionSpecificationType EST) : Type(EST) {}
4528 
4529  void instantiate();
4530  };
4531 
4532  /// Extra information about a function prototype. ExtProtoInfo is not
4533  /// stored as such in FunctionProtoType but is used to group together
4534  /// the various bits of extra information about a function prototype.
4535  struct ExtProtoInfo {
4536  FunctionType::ExtInfo ExtInfo;
4537  unsigned Variadic : 1;
4538  unsigned HasTrailingReturn : 1;
4539  unsigned AArch64SMEAttributes : 8;
4540  Qualifiers TypeQuals;
4541  RefQualifierKind RefQualifier = RQ_None;
4542  ExceptionSpecInfo ExceptionSpec;
4543  const ExtParameterInfo *ExtParameterInfos = nullptr;
4544  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
4545 
4546  ExtProtoInfo()
4547  : Variadic(false), HasTrailingReturn(false),
4548  AArch64SMEAttributes(SME_NormalFunction) {}
4549 
4550  ExtProtoInfo(CallingConv CC)
4551  : ExtInfo(CC), Variadic(false), HasTrailingReturn(false),
4552  AArch64SMEAttributes(SME_NormalFunction) {}
4553 
4554  ExtProtoInfo withExceptionSpec(const ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI) {
4555  ExtProtoInfo Result(*this);
4556  Result.ExceptionSpec = ESI;
4557  return Result;
4558  }
4559 
4560  bool requiresFunctionProtoTypeExtraBitfields() const {
4561  return ExceptionSpec.Type == EST_Dynamic ||
4562  requiresFunctionProtoTypeArmAttributes();
4563  }
4564 
4565  bool requiresFunctionProtoTypeArmAttributes() const {
4566  return AArch64SMEAttributes != SME_NormalFunction;
4567  }
4568 
4569  void setArmSMEAttribute(AArch64SMETypeAttributes Kind, bool Enable = true) {
4570  if (Enable)
4571  AArch64SMEAttributes |= Kind;
4572  else
4573  AArch64SMEAttributes &= ~Kind;
4574  }
4575  };

4610  /// Determine whether there are any argument types that
4611  /// contain an unexpanded parameter pack.
4612  static bool containsAnyUnexpandedParameterPack(const QualType *ArgArray,
4613  unsigned numArgs) {

4624  /// This struct is returned by getExceptionSpecSize and is used to
4625  /// translate an ExceptionSpecificationType to the number and kind
4626  /// of trailing objects related to the exception specification.
4627  struct ExceptionSpecSizeHolder {
4628  unsigned NumExceptionType;
4629  unsigned NumExprPtr;
4630  unsigned NumFunctionDeclPtr;
4631  };
4632 
4633  /// Return the number and kind of trailing objects
4634  /// related to the exception specification.
4635  static ExceptionSpecSizeHolder
4636  getExceptionSpecSize(ExceptionSpecificationType EST, unsigned NumExceptions) {
4637  switch (EST) {
4638  case EST_None:
4639  case EST_DynamicNone:
4640  case EST_MSAny:
4641  case EST_BasicNoexcept:
4642  case EST_Unparsed:
4643  case EST_NoThrow:
4644  return {0, 0, 0};
4645 
4646  case EST_Dynamic:
4647  return {NumExceptions, 0, 0};
4648 
4649  case EST_DependentNoexcept:
4650  case EST_NoexceptFalse:
4651  case EST_NoexceptTrue:
4652  return {0, 1, 0};
4653 
4654  case EST_Uninstantiated:
4655  return {0, 0, 2};
4656 
4657  case EST_Unevaluated:
4658  return {0, 0, 1};
4659  }
4660  llvm_unreachable("bad exception specification kind");
4661  }
4662 
4663  /// Return the number and kind of trailing objects
4664  /// related to the exception specification.
4665  ExceptionSpecSizeHolder getExceptionSpecSize() const {
4666  return getExceptionSpecSize(getExceptionSpecType(), getNumExceptions());
4667  }
4668 
4669  /// Whether the trailing FunctionTypeExtraBitfields is present.
4670  bool hasExtraBitfields() const {
4671  assert((getExceptionSpecType() != EST_Dynamic ||
4672  FunctionTypeBits.HasExtraBitfields) &&
4673  "ExtraBitfields are required for given ExceptionSpecType");
4674  return FunctionTypeBits.HasExtraBitfields;
4675 
4676  }
4677 
4678  bool hasArmTypeAttributes() const {
4679  return FunctionTypeBits.HasExtraBitfields &&
4680  getTrailingObjects<FunctionTypeExtraBitfields>()
4681  ->HasArmTypeAttributes;
4682  }

4737  /// spec.

4740  /// Return all the available information about this type's exception spec.
4741  ExceptionSpecInfo getExceptionSpecInfo() const {
4742  ExceptionSpecInfo Result;
4743  Result.Type = getExceptionSpecType();
4744  if (Result.Type == EST_Dynamic) {
4745  Result.Exceptions = exceptions();
4746  } else if (isComputedNoexcept(Result.Type)) {
4747  Result.NoexceptExpr = getNoexceptExpr();
4748  } else if (Result.Type == EST_Uninstantiated) {
4749  Result.SourceDecl = getExceptionSpecDecl();
4750  Result.SourceTemplate = getExceptionSpecTemplate();
4751  } else if (Result.Type == EST_Unevaluated) {
4752  Result.SourceDecl = getExceptionSpecDecl();
4753  }
4754  return Result;
4755  }
4756 
4757  /// Return the number of types in the exception specification.
4758  unsigned getNumExceptions() const {
4759  return getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Dynamic
4760  ? getTrailingObjects<FunctionTypeExtraBitfields>()
4761  ->NumExceptionType
4762  : 0;
4763  }

4766  QualType getExceptionType(unsigned i) const {
4767  assert(i < getNumExceptions() && "Invalid exception number!");
4768  return exception_begin()[i];
4769  }

4771  /// Return the expression inside noexcept(expression), or a null pointer
4772  /// if there is none (because the exception spec is not of this form).
4773  Expr *getNoexceptExpr() const {
4774  if (!isComputedNoexcept(getExceptionSpecType()))
4775  return nullptr;
4776  return *getTrailingObjects<Expr *>();
4777  }

4779  /// If this function type has an exception specification which hasn't
4780  /// been determined yet (either because it has not been evaluated or because
4781  /// it has not been instantiated), this is the function whose exception
4782  /// specification is represented by this type.
4783  FunctionDecl *getExceptionSpecDecl() const {
4784  if (getExceptionSpecType() != EST_Uninstantiated &&
4785  getExceptionSpecType() != EST_Unevaluated)
4786  return nullptr;
4787  return getTrailingObjects<FunctionDecl *>()[0];
4788  }

4791  /// specification, this is the function whose exception specification

4795  if (getExceptionSpecType() != EST_Uninstantiated)
4796  return nullptr;
4797  return getTrailingObjects<FunctionDecl *>()[1];
4798  }

5198 class PackIndexingType final

5221

5223  if (hasSelectedType())
5224  return getSelectedType();
5225  return QualType(this, 0);
5226  }

5392 /// An attributed type is a type to which a type attribute has been applied.
5393 ///
5394 /// The "modified type" is the fully-sugared type to which the attributed
5395 /// type was applied; generally it is not canonically equivalent to the
5396 /// attributed type. The "equivalent type" is the minimally-desugared type
5397 /// which the type is canonically equivalent to.
5398 ///
5399 /// For example, in the following attributed type:
5400 /// int32_t __attribute__((vector_size(16)))
5401 /// - the modified type is the TypedefType for int32_t
5402 /// - the equivalent type is VectorType(16, int32_t)
5403 /// - the canonical type is VectorType(16, int)
5404 class AttributedType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
5405 public:
5406  using Kind = attr::Kind;
5407 
5408 private:
5409  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
5410 
5411  QualType ModifiedType;
5412  QualType EquivalentType;
5413 
5414  AttributedType(QualType canon, attr::Kind attrKind, QualType modified,
5415  QualType equivalent)
5416  : Type(Attributed, canon, equivalent->getDependence()),
5417  ModifiedType(modified), EquivalentType(equivalent) {
5418  AttributedTypeBits.AttrKind = attrKind;
5419  }
5420 
5421 public:
5422  Kind getAttrKind() const {
5423  return static_cast<Kind>(AttributedTypeBits.AttrKind);
5424  }
5425 
5426  QualType getModifiedType() const { return ModifiedType; }
5427  QualType getEquivalentType() const { return EquivalentType; }
5428 
5429  bool isSugared() const { return true; }
5430  QualType desugar() const { return getEquivalentType(); }
5431 
5432  /// Does this attribute behave like a type qualifier?
5433  ///
5434  /// A type qualifier adjusts a type to provide specialized rules for
5435  /// a specific object, like the standard const and volatile qualifiers.
5436  /// This includes attributes controlling things like nullability,
5437  /// address spaces, and ARC ownership. The value of the object is still
5438  /// largely described by the modified type.
5439  ///
5440  /// In contrast, many type attributes "rewrite" their modified type to
5441  /// produce a fundamentally different type, not necessarily related in any
5442  /// formalizable way to the original type. For example, calling convention
5443  /// and vector attributes are not simple type qualifiers.
5444  ///
5445  /// Type qualifiers are often, but not always, reflected in the canonical
5446  /// type.
5447  bool isQualifier() const;
5448 
5449  bool isMSTypeSpec() const;
5450 
5451  bool isWebAssemblyFuncrefSpec() const;
5452 
5453  bool isCallingConv() const;
5454 
5455  std::optional<NullabilityKind> getImmediateNullability() const;
5456 
5457  /// Retrieve the attribute kind corresponding to the given
5458  /// nullability kind.
5459  static Kind getNullabilityAttrKind(NullabilityKind kind) {
5460  switch (kind) {
5461  case NullabilityKind::NonNull:
5462  return attr::TypeNonNull;
5463 
5464  case NullabilityKind::Nullable:
5465  return attr::TypeNullable;
5466 
5467  case NullabilityKind::NullableResult:
5468  return attr::TypeNullableResult;
5469 
5470  case NullabilityKind::Unspecified:
5471  return attr::TypeNullUnspecified;
5472  }
5473  llvm_unreachable("Unknown nullability kind.");
5474  }
5475 
5476  /// Strip off the top-level nullability annotation on the given
5477  /// type, if it's there.
5478  ///
5479  /// \param T The type to strip. If the type is exactly an
5480  /// AttributedType specifying nullability (without looking through
5481  /// type sugar), the nullability is returned and this type changed
5482  /// to the underlying modified type.
5483  ///
5484  /// \returns the top-level nullability, if present.
5485  static std::optional<NullabilityKind> stripOuterNullability(QualType &T);
5486 
5487  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
5488  Profile(ID, getAttrKind(), ModifiedType, EquivalentType);
5489  }
5490 
5491  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, Kind attrKind,
5492  QualType modified, QualType equivalent) {
5493  ID.AddInteger(attrKind);
5494  ID.AddPointer(modified.getAsOpaquePtr());
5495  ID.AddPointer(equivalent.getAsOpaquePtr());
5496  }
5497 
5498  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5499  return T->getTypeClass() == Attributed;
5500  }
5501 };
5502

5506 
5507  QualType WrappedType;
5508  const BTFTypeTagAttr *BTFAttr;

5510  BTFTagAttributedType(QualType Canon, QualType Wrapped,

5518

5520  QualType desugar() const { return getWrappedType(); }
5521

5537 class TemplateTypeParmType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
5538  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
5539 
5540  // Helper data collector for canonical types.
5541  struct CanonicalTTPTInfo {
5542  unsigned Depth : 15;
5543  unsigned ParameterPack : 1;
5544  unsigned Index : 16;
5545  };
5546 
5547  union {
5548  // Info for the canonical type.
5549  CanonicalTTPTInfo CanTTPTInfo;
5550 
5551  // Info for the non-canonical type.
5552  TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTPDecl;
5553  };
5554 
5555  /// Build a non-canonical type.
5556  TemplateTypeParmType(TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTPDecl, QualType Canon)
5557  : Type(TemplateTypeParm, Canon,
5558  TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation |
5559  (Canon->getDependence() & TypeDependence::UnexpandedPack)),
5560  TTPDecl(TTPDecl) {}
5561 
5562  /// Build the canonical type.
5563  TemplateTypeParmType(unsigned D, unsigned I, bool PP)
5564  : Type(TemplateTypeParm, QualType(this, 0),
5565  TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation |
5566  (PP ? TypeDependence::UnexpandedPack : TypeDependence::None)) {
5567  CanTTPTInfo.Depth = D;
5568  CanTTPTInfo.Index = I;
5569  CanTTPTInfo.ParameterPack = PP;
5570  }
5571 
5572  const CanonicalTTPTInfo& getCanTTPTInfo() const {
5573  QualType Can = getCanonicalTypeInternal();
5574  return Can->castAs<TemplateTypeParmType>()->CanTTPTInfo;
5575  }
5576 
5577 public:
5578  unsigned getDepth() const { return getCanTTPTInfo().Depth; }
5579  unsigned getIndex() const { return getCanTTPTInfo().Index; }
5580  bool isParameterPack() const { return getCanTTPTInfo().ParameterPack; }
5581 
5582  TemplateTypeParmDecl *getDecl() const {
5583  return isCanonicalUnqualified() ? nullptr : TTPDecl;
5584  }
5585 
5586  IdentifierInfo *getIdentifier() const;
5587 
5588  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
5589  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
5590 
5591  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
5592  Profile(ID, getDepth(), getIndex(), isParameterPack(), getDecl());
5593  }
5594 
5595  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, unsigned Depth,
5596  unsigned Index, bool ParameterPack,
5597  TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTPDecl) {
5598  ID.AddInteger(Depth);
5599  ID.AddInteger(Index);
5600  ID.AddBoolean(ParameterPack);
5601  ID.AddPointer(TTPDecl);
5602  }
5603 
5604  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5605  return T->getTypeClass() == TemplateTypeParm;
5606  }
5607 };

5609 /// Represents the result of substituting a type for a template
5610 /// type parameter.
5611 ///
5612 /// Within an instantiated template, all template type parameters have
5613 /// been replaced with these. They are used solely to record that a
5614 /// type was originally written as a template type parameter;
5615 /// therefore they are never canonical.
5616 class SubstTemplateTypeParmType final
5617  : public Type,
5618  public llvm::FoldingSetNode,
5619  private llvm::TrailingObjects<SubstTemplateTypeParmType, QualType> {

5621  friend class llvm::TrailingObjects<SubstTemplateTypeParmType, QualType>;
5622 
5623  Decl *AssociatedDecl;
5624 
5625  SubstTemplateTypeParmType(QualType Replacement, Decl *AssociatedDecl,
5626  unsigned Index, std::optional<unsigned> PackIndex);
5627 
5628 public:
5629  /// Gets the type that was substituted for the template
5630  /// parameter.
5631  QualType getReplacementType() const {
5632  return SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeBits.HasNonCanonicalUnderlyingType
5633  ? *getTrailingObjects<QualType>()
5634  : getCanonicalTypeInternal();
5635  }
5636 
5637  /// A template-like entity which owns the whole pattern being substituted.
5638  /// This will usually own a set of template parameters, or in some
5639  /// cases might even be a template parameter itself.
5640  Decl *getAssociatedDecl() const { return AssociatedDecl; }
5641 
5642  /// Gets the template parameter declaration that was substituted for.
5643  const TemplateTypeParmDecl *getReplacedParameter() const;
5644 
5645  /// Returns the index of the replaced parameter in the associated declaration.
5646  /// This should match the result of `getReplacedParameter()->getIndex()`.
5647  unsigned getIndex() const { return SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeBits.Index; }
5648 
5649  std::optional<unsigned> getPackIndex() const {
5650  if (SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeBits.PackIndex == 0)
5651  return std::nullopt;
5652  return SubstTemplateTypeParmTypeBits.PackIndex - 1;
5653  }
5654 
5655  bool isSugared() const { return true; }
5656  QualType desugar() const { return getReplacementType(); }
5657 
5658  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
5659  Profile(ID, getReplacementType(), getAssociatedDecl(), getIndex(),
5660  getPackIndex());
5661  }
5662 
5663  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, QualType Replacement,
5664  const Decl *AssociatedDecl, unsigned Index,
5665  std::optional<unsigned> PackIndex) {
5666  Replacement.Profile(ID);
5667  ID.AddPointer(AssociatedDecl);
5668  ID.AddInteger(Index);
5669  ID.AddInteger(PackIndex ? *PackIndex - 1 : 0);
5670  }
5671 
5672  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5673  return T->getTypeClass() == SubstTemplateTypeParm;
5674  }
5675 };
5676 
5677 /// Represents the result of substituting a set of types for a template
5678 /// type parameter pack.
5679 ///
5680 /// When a pack expansion in the source code contains multiple parameter packs
5681 /// and those parameter packs correspond to different levels of template
5682 /// parameter lists, this type node is used to represent a template type
5683 /// parameter pack from an outer level, which has already had its argument pack
5684 /// substituted but that still lives within a pack expansion that itself
5685 /// could not be instantiated. When actually performing a substitution into
5686 /// that pack expansion (e.g., when all template parameters have corresponding
5687 /// arguments), this type will be replaced with the \c SubstTemplateTypeParmType
5688 /// at the current pack substitution index.
5689 class SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
5690  friend class ASTContext;
5691 
5692  /// A pointer to the set of template arguments that this
5693  /// parameter pack is instantiated with.
5694  const TemplateArgument *Arguments;
5695 
5696  llvm::PointerIntPair<Decl *, 1, bool> AssociatedDeclAndFinal;
5697 
5698  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(QualType Canon, Decl *AssociatedDecl,
5699  unsigned Index, bool Final,
5700  const TemplateArgument &ArgPack);
5701 
5702 public:
5703  IdentifierInfo *getIdentifier() const;
5704 
5705  /// A template-like entity which owns the whole pattern being substituted.
5706  /// This will usually own a set of template parameters, or in some
5707  /// cases might even be a template parameter itself.
5708  Decl *getAssociatedDecl() const;
5709 
5710  /// Gets the template parameter declaration that was substituted for.
5711  const TemplateTypeParmDecl *getReplacedParameter() const;
5712 
5713  /// Returns the index of the replaced parameter in the associated declaration.
5714  /// This should match the result of `getReplacedParameter()->getIndex()`.
5715  unsigned getIndex() const { return SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeBits.Index; }
5716 
5717  // When true the substitution will be 'Final' (subst node won't be placed).
5718  bool getFinal() const;
5719 
5720  unsigned getNumArgs() const {
5721  return SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeBits.NumArgs;
5722  }
5723 
5724  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
5725  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
5726 
5727  TemplateArgument getArgumentPack() const;
5728 
5729  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID);
5730  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const Decl *AssociatedDecl,
5731  unsigned Index, bool Final,
5732  const TemplateArgument &ArgPack);
5733 
5734  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5735  return T->getTypeClass() == SubstTemplateTypeParmPack;
5736  }
5737 };

5739 /// Common base class for placeholders for types that get replaced by
5740 /// placeholder type deduction: C++11 auto, C++14 decltype(auto), C++17 deduced
5741 /// class template types, and constrained type names.
5742 ///
5743 /// These types are usually a placeholder for a deduced type. However, before
5744 /// the initializer is attached, or (usually) if the initializer is
5745 /// type-dependent, there is no deduced type and the type is canonical. In
5746 /// the latter case, it is also a dependent type.
5747 class DeducedType : public Type {
5748  QualType DeducedAsType;
5749 
5750 protected:
5751  DeducedType(TypeClass TC, QualType DeducedAsType,
5752  TypeDependence ExtraDependence, QualType Canon)
5753  : Type(TC, Canon,
5754  ExtraDependence | (DeducedAsType.isNull()
5755  ? TypeDependence::None
5756  : DeducedAsType->getDependence() &
5757  ~TypeDependence::VariablyModified)),
5758  DeducedAsType(DeducedAsType) {}
5759 
5760 public:
5761  bool isSugared() const { return !DeducedAsType.isNull(); }
5762  QualType desugar() const {
5763  return isSugared() ? DeducedAsType : QualType(this, 0);
5764  }
5765 
5766  /// Get the type deduced for this placeholder type, or null if it
5767  /// has not been deduced.
5768  QualType getDeducedType() const { return DeducedAsType; }
5769  bool isDeduced() const {
5770  return !DeducedAsType.isNull() || isDependentType();
5771  }
5772 
5773  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5774  return T->getTypeClass() == Auto ||
5775  T->getTypeClass() == DeducedTemplateSpecialization;
5776  }
5777 };
5778 
5779 /// Represents a C++11 auto or C++14 decltype(auto) type, possibly constrained
5780 /// by a type-constraint.
5781 class AutoType : public DeducedType, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {

5783 
5784  ConceptDecl *TypeConstraintConcept;

5786  AutoType(QualType DeducedAsType, AutoTypeKeyword Keyword,

5788  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TypeConstraintArgs);
5789 
5790 public:

5792  return {reinterpret_cast<const TemplateArgument *>(this + 1),
5793  AutoTypeBits.NumArgs};
5794  }
5795 
5796  ConceptDecl *getTypeConstraintConcept() const {
5797  return TypeConstraintConcept;
5798  }
5799 
5800  bool isConstrained() const {
5801  return TypeConstraintConcept != nullptr;
5802  }
5803 
5804  bool isDecltypeAuto() const {
5805  return getKeyword() == AutoTypeKeyword::DecltypeAuto;
5806  }
5807 
5808  bool isGNUAutoType() const {
5809  return getKeyword() == AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType;
5810  }
5811 
5812  AutoTypeKeyword getKeyword() const {
5813  return (AutoTypeKeyword)AutoTypeBits.Keyword;
5814  }
5815 
5816  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const ASTContext &Context);
5817  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const ASTContext &Context,
5818  QualType Deduced, AutoTypeKeyword Keyword,
5819  bool IsDependent, ConceptDecl *CD,
5820  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Arguments);
5821 
5822  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5823  return T->getTypeClass() == Auto;
5824  }
5825 };

5827 /// Represents a C++17 deduced template specialization type.
5828 class DeducedTemplateSpecializationType : public DeducedType,
5829  public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
5830  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
5831 
5832  /// The name of the template whose arguments will be deduced.
5833  TemplateName Template;
5834 
5835  DeducedTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName Template,
5836  QualType DeducedAsType,
5837  bool IsDeducedAsDependent)
5838  : DeducedType(DeducedTemplateSpecialization, DeducedAsType,
5839  toTypeDependence(Template.getDependence()) |
5840  (IsDeducedAsDependent
5841  ? TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation
5842  : TypeDependence::None),
5843  DeducedAsType.isNull() ? QualType(this, 0)
5844  : DeducedAsType.getCanonicalType()),
5845  Template(Template) {}
5846 
5847 public:
5848  /// Retrieve the name of the template that we are deducing.
5849  TemplateName getTemplateName() const { return Template;}
5850 
5851  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
5852  Profile(ID, getTemplateName(), getDeducedType(), isDependentType());
5853  }
5854 
5855  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, TemplateName Template,
5856  QualType Deduced, bool IsDependent) {
5857  Template.Profile(ID);
5858  QualType CanonicalType =
5859  Deduced.isNull() ? Deduced : Deduced.getCanonicalType();
5860  ID.AddPointer(CanonicalType.getAsOpaquePtr());
5861  ID.AddBoolean(IsDependent || Template.isDependent());
5862  }
5863 
5864  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5865  return T->getTypeClass() == DeducedTemplateSpecialization;
5866  }
5867 };
5868 
5869 /// Represents a type template specialization; the template
5870 /// must be a class template, a type alias template, or a template
5871 /// template parameter. A template which cannot be resolved to one of
5872 /// these, e.g. because it is written with a dependent scope
5873 /// specifier, is instead represented as a
5874 /// @c DependentTemplateSpecializationType.
5875 ///
5876 /// A non-dependent template specialization type is always "sugar",
5877 /// typically for a \c RecordType. For example, a class template
5878 /// specialization type of \c vector<int> will refer to a tag type for
5879 /// the instantiation \c std::vector<int, std::allocator<int>>
5880 ///
5881 /// Template specializations are dependent if either the template or
5882 /// any of the template arguments are dependent, in which case the
5883 /// type may also be canonical.
5884 ///
5885 /// Instances of this type are allocated with a trailing array of
5886 /// TemplateArguments, followed by a QualType representing the
5887 /// non-canonical aliased type when the template is a type alias
5888 /// template.
5889 class TemplateSpecializationType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
5890  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
5891 
5892  /// The name of the template being specialized. This is
5893  /// either a TemplateName::Template (in which case it is a
5894  /// ClassTemplateDecl*, a TemplateTemplateParmDecl*, or a
5895  /// TypeAliasTemplateDecl*), a
5896  /// TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack, or a
5897  /// TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm (in which case the
5898  /// replacement must, recursively, be one of these).
5899  TemplateName Template;
5900 
5901  TemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName T,
5902  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
5903  QualType Canon,
5904  QualType Aliased);
5905 
5906 public:
5907  /// Determine whether any of the given template arguments are dependent.
5908  ///
5909  /// The converted arguments should be supplied when known; whether an
5910  /// argument is dependent can depend on the conversions performed on it
5911  /// (for example, a 'const int' passed as a template argument might be
5912  /// dependent if the parameter is a reference but non-dependent if the
5913  /// parameter is an int).
5914  ///
5915  /// Note that the \p Args parameter is unused: this is intentional, to remind
5916  /// the caller that they need to pass in the converted arguments, not the
5917  /// specified arguments.
5918  static bool
5919  anyDependentTemplateArguments(ArrayRef<TemplateArgumentLoc> Args,
5920  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Converted);
5921  static bool
5922  anyDependentTemplateArguments(const TemplateArgumentListInfo &,
5923  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Converted);
5924  static bool anyInstantiationDependentTemplateArguments(
5925  ArrayRef<TemplateArgumentLoc> Args);
5926 
5927  /// True if this template specialization type matches a current
5928  /// instantiation in the context in which it is found.
5929  bool isCurrentInstantiation() const {
5930  return isa<InjectedClassNameType>(getCanonicalTypeInternal());
5931  }
5932 
5933  /// Determine if this template specialization type is for a type alias
5934  /// template that has been substituted.
5935  ///
5936  /// Nearly every template specialization type whose template is an alias
5937  /// template will be substituted. However, this is not the case when
5938  /// the specialization contains a pack expansion but the template alias
5939  /// does not have a corresponding parameter pack, e.g.,
5940  ///
5941  /// \code
5942  /// template<typename T, typename U, typename V> struct S;
5943  /// template<typename T, typename U> using A = S<T, int, U>;
5944  /// template<typename... Ts> struct X {
5945  /// typedef A<Ts...> type; // not a type alias
5946  /// };
5947  /// \endcode
5948  bool isTypeAlias() const { return TemplateSpecializationTypeBits.TypeAlias; }
5949 
5950  /// Get the aliased type, if this is a specialization of a type alias
5951  /// template.
5952  QualType getAliasedType() const;
5953 
5954  /// Retrieve the name of the template that we are specializing.
5955  TemplateName getTemplateName() const { return Template; }
5956 
5957  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> template_arguments() const {
5958  return {reinterpret_cast<const TemplateArgument *>(this + 1),
5959  TemplateSpecializationTypeBits.NumArgs};
5960  }
5961 
5962  bool isSugared() const {
5963  return !isDependentType() || isCurrentInstantiation() || isTypeAlias();
5964  }
5965 
5966  QualType desugar() const {
5967  return isTypeAlias() ? getAliasedType() : getCanonicalTypeInternal();
5968  }
5969 
5970  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, const ASTContext &Ctx);
5971  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, TemplateName T,
5972  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
5973  const ASTContext &Context);
5974 
5975  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
5976  return T->getTypeClass() == TemplateSpecialization;
5977  }
5978 };
5979 
5980 /// Print a template argument list, including the '<' and '>'
5981 /// enclosing the template arguments.
5982 void printTemplateArgumentList(raw_ostream &OS,
5983  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
5984  const PrintingPolicy &Policy,
5985  const TemplateParameterList *TPL = nullptr);
5986 
5987 void printTemplateArgumentList(raw_ostream &OS,
5988  ArrayRef<TemplateArgumentLoc> Args,
5989  const PrintingPolicy &Policy,
5990  const TemplateParameterList *TPL = nullptr);
5991 
5992 void printTemplateArgumentList(raw_ostream &OS,
5993  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
5994  const PrintingPolicy &Policy,
5995  const TemplateParameterList *TPL = nullptr);
5996 
5997 /// Make a best-effort determination of whether the type T can be produced by
5998 /// substituting Args into the default argument of Param.
5999 bool isSubstitutedDefaultArgument(ASTContext &Ctx, TemplateArgument Arg,
6000  const NamedDecl *Param,
6001  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
6002  unsigned Depth);
6003 
6004 /// The injected class name of a C++ class template or class
6005 /// template partial specialization. Used to record that a type was
6006 /// spelled with a bare identifier rather than as a template-id; the
6007 /// equivalent for non-templated classes is just RecordType.
6008 ///
6009 /// Injected class name types are always dependent. Template
6010 /// instantiation turns these into RecordTypes.
6011 ///
6012 /// Injected class name types are always canonical. This works
6013 /// because it is impossible to compare an injected class name type
6014 /// with the corresponding non-injected template type, for the same
6015 /// reason that it is impossible to directly compare template
6016 /// parameters from different dependent contexts: injected class name
6017 /// types can only occur within the scope of a particular templated
6018 /// declaration, and within that scope every template specialization
6019 /// will canonicalize to the injected class name (when appropriate
6020 /// according to the rules of the language).
6021 class InjectedClassNameType : public Type {
6022  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these.
6023  friend class ASTNodeImporter;
6024  friend class ASTReader; // FIXME: ASTContext::getInjectedClassNameType is not
6025  // currently suitable for AST reading, too much
6026  // interdependencies.
6027  template <class T> friend class serialization::AbstractTypeReader;
6028 
6029  CXXRecordDecl *Decl;
6030 
6031  /// The template specialization which this type represents.
6032  /// For example, in
6033  /// template <class T> class A { ... };
6034  /// this is A<T>, whereas in
6035  /// template <class X, class Y> class A<B<X,Y> > { ... };
6036  /// this is A<B<X,Y> >.
6037  ///
6038  /// It is always unqualified, always a template specialization type,
6039  /// and always dependent.
6040  QualType InjectedType;
6041 
6042  InjectedClassNameType(CXXRecordDecl *D, QualType TST)
6043  : Type(InjectedClassName, QualType(),
6044  TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation),
6045  Decl(D), InjectedType(TST) {
6046  assert(isa<TemplateSpecializationType>(TST));
6047  assert(!TST.hasQualifiers());
6048  assert(TST->isDependentType());
6049  }
6050 
6051 public:
6052  QualType getInjectedSpecializationType() const { return InjectedType; }
6053 
6054  const TemplateSpecializationType *getInjectedTST() const {
6055  return cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(InjectedType.getTypePtr());
6056  }
6057 
6058  TemplateName getTemplateName() const {
6059  return getInjectedTST()->getTemplateName();
6060  }
6061 
6062  CXXRecordDecl *getDecl() const;
6063 
6064  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6065  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6066 
6067  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6068  return T->getTypeClass() == InjectedClassName;
6069  }
6070 };
6071 
6072 /// The elaboration keyword that precedes a qualified type name or
6073 /// introduces an elaborated-type-specifier.
6074 enum class ElaboratedTypeKeyword {
6075  /// The "struct" keyword introduces the elaborated-type-specifier.
6076  Struct,
6077 
6078  /// The "__interface" keyword introduces the elaborated-type-specifier.
6079  Interface,
6080 
6081  /// The "union" keyword introduces the elaborated-type-specifier.
6082  Union,
6083 
6084  /// The "class" keyword introduces the elaborated-type-specifier.
6085  Class,
6086 
6087  /// The "enum" keyword introduces the elaborated-type-specifier.
6088  Enum,
6089 
6090  /// The "typename" keyword precedes the qualified type name, e.g.,
6091  /// \c typename T::type.
6092  Typename,
6093 
6094  /// No keyword precedes the qualified type name.
6095  None
6096 };
6097 
6098 /// The kind of a tag type.
6099 enum class TagTypeKind {
6100  /// The "struct" keyword.
6101  Struct,
6102 
6103  /// The "__interface" keyword.
6104  Interface,
6105 
6106  /// The "union" keyword.
6107  Union,
6108 
6109  /// The "class" keyword.
6110  Class,
6111 
6112  /// The "enum" keyword.
6113  Enum
6114 };

6116 /// A helper class for Type nodes having an ElaboratedTypeKeyword.

6126  }
6127 
6128 public:

6130  return static_cast<ElaboratedTypeKeyword>(TypeWithKeywordBits.Keyword);
6131  }
6132 
6133  /// Converts a type specifier (DeclSpec::TST) into an elaborated type keyword.
6134  static ElaboratedTypeKeyword getKeywordForTypeSpec(unsigned TypeSpec);
6135 
6136  /// Converts a type specifier (DeclSpec::TST) into a tag type kind.
6137  /// It is an error to provide a type specifier which *isn't* a tag kind here.
6138  static TagTypeKind getTagTypeKindForTypeSpec(unsigned TypeSpec);
6139 
6140  /// Converts a TagTypeKind into an elaborated type keyword.
6141  static ElaboratedTypeKeyword getKeywordForTagTypeKind(TagTypeKind Tag);
6142

6147

6149

6151

6154  }

6156  class CannotCastToThisType {};

6160 /// Represents a type that was referred to using an elaborated type
6161 /// keyword, e.g., struct S, or via a qualified name, e.g., N::M::type,
6162 /// or both.
6163 ///
6164 /// This type is used to keep track of a type name as written in the
6165 /// source code, including tag keywords and any nested-name-specifiers.
6166 /// The type itself is always "sugar", used to express what was written
6167 /// in the source code but containing no additional semantic information.
6168 class ElaboratedType final
6169  : public TypeWithKeyword,
6170  public llvm::FoldingSetNode,
6171  private llvm::TrailingObjects<ElaboratedType, TagDecl *> {
6172  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
6173  friend TrailingObjects;
6174 
6175  /// The nested name specifier containing the qualifier.
6176  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS;
6177 
6178  /// The type that this qualified name refers to.
6179  QualType NamedType;
6180 
6181  /// The (re)declaration of this tag type owned by this occurrence is stored
6182  /// as a trailing object if there is one. Use getOwnedTagDecl to obtain
6183  /// it, or obtain a null pointer if there is none.
6184 
6185  ElaboratedType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword, NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
6186  QualType NamedType, QualType CanonType, TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl)
6187  : TypeWithKeyword(Keyword, Elaborated, CanonType,
6188  // Any semantic dependence on the qualifier will have
6189  // been incorporated into NamedType. We still need to
6190  // track syntactic (instantiation / error / pack)
6191  // dependence on the qualifier.
6192  NamedType->getDependence() |
6193  (NNS ? toSyntacticDependence(
6194  toTypeDependence(NNS->getDependence()))
6195  : TypeDependence::None)),
6196  NNS(NNS), NamedType(NamedType) {
6197  ElaboratedTypeBits.HasOwnedTagDecl = false;
6198  if (OwnedTagDecl) {
6199  ElaboratedTypeBits.HasOwnedTagDecl = true;
6200  *getTrailingObjects<TagDecl *>() = OwnedTagDecl;
6201  }
6202  }
6203 
6204 public:
6205  /// Retrieve the qualification on this type.
6206  NestedNameSpecifier *getQualifier() const { return NNS; }
6207 
6208  /// Retrieve the type named by the qualified-id.
6209  QualType getNamedType() const { return NamedType; }
6210 
6211  /// Remove a single level of sugar.
6212  QualType desugar() const { return getNamedType(); }
6213 
6214  /// Returns whether this type directly provides sugar.
6215  bool isSugared() const { return true; }
6216 
6217  /// Return the (re)declaration of this type owned by this occurrence of this
6218  /// type, or nullptr if there is none.
6219  TagDecl *getOwnedTagDecl() const {
6220  return ElaboratedTypeBits.HasOwnedTagDecl ? *getTrailingObjects<TagDecl *>()
6221  : nullptr;
6222  }
6223 
6224  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
6225  Profile(ID, getKeyword(), NNS, NamedType, getOwnedTagDecl());
6226  }
6227 
6228  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
6229  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS, QualType NamedType,
6230  TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl) {
6231  ID.AddInteger(llvm::to_underlying(Keyword));
6232  ID.AddPointer(NNS);
6233  NamedType.Profile(ID);
6234  ID.AddPointer(OwnedTagDecl);
6235  }
6236 
6237  static bool classof(const Type *T) { return T->getTypeClass() == Elaborated; }
6238 };
6239 
6240 /// Represents a qualified type name for which the type name is
6241 /// dependent.
6242 ///
6243 /// DependentNameType represents a class of dependent types that involve a
6244 /// possibly dependent nested-name-specifier (e.g., "T::") followed by a
6245 /// name of a type. The DependentNameType may start with a "typename" (for a
6246 /// typename-specifier), "class", "struct", "union", or "enum" (for a
6247 /// dependent elaborated-type-specifier), or nothing (in contexts where we
6248 /// know that we must be referring to a type, e.g., in a base class specifier).
6249 /// Typically the nested-name-specifier is dependent, but in MSVC compatibility
6250 /// mode, this type is used with non-dependent names to delay name lookup until
6251 /// instantiation.
6252 class DependentNameType : public TypeWithKeyword, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
6253  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
6254 
6255  /// The nested name specifier containing the qualifier.
6256  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS;
6257 
6258  /// The type that this typename specifier refers to.
6259  const IdentifierInfo *Name;
6260 
6261  DependentNameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword, NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
6262  const IdentifierInfo *Name, QualType CanonType)
6263  : TypeWithKeyword(Keyword, DependentName, CanonType,
6264  TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation |
6265  toTypeDependence(NNS->getDependence())),
6266  NNS(NNS), Name(Name) {}
6267 
6268 public:
6269  /// Retrieve the qualification on this type.
6270  NestedNameSpecifier *getQualifier() const { return NNS; }
6271 
6272  /// Retrieve the type named by the typename specifier as an identifier.
6273  ///
6274  /// This routine will return a non-NULL identifier pointer when the
6275  /// form of the original typename was terminated by an identifier,
6276  /// e.g., "typename T::type".
6277  const IdentifierInfo *getIdentifier() const {
6278  return Name;
6279  }
6280 
6281  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6282  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6283 
6284  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
6285  Profile(ID, getKeyword(), NNS, Name);
6286  }
6287 
6288  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
6289  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS, const IdentifierInfo *Name) {
6290  ID.AddInteger(llvm::to_underlying(Keyword));
6291  ID.AddPointer(NNS);
6292  ID.AddPointer(Name);
6293  }
6294 
6295  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6296  return T->getTypeClass() == DependentName;
6297  }
6298 };

6347 /// Represents a pack expansion of types.
6348 ///
6349 /// Pack expansions are part of C++11 variadic templates. A pack
6350 /// expansion contains a pattern, which itself contains one or more
6351 /// "unexpanded" parameter packs. When instantiated, a pack expansion
6352 /// produces a series of types, each instantiated from the pattern of
6353 /// the expansion, where the Ith instantiation of the pattern uses the
6354 /// Ith arguments bound to each of the unexpanded parameter packs. The
6355 /// pack expansion is considered to "expand" these unexpanded
6356 /// parameter packs.
6357 ///
6358 /// \code
6359 /// template<typename ...Types> struct tuple;
6360 ///
6361 /// template<typename ...Types>
6362 /// struct tuple_of_references {
6363 /// typedef tuple<Types&...> type;
6364 /// };
6365 /// \endcode
6366 ///
6367 /// Here, the pack expansion \c Types&... is represented via a
6368 /// PackExpansionType whose pattern is Types&.
6369 class PackExpansionType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
6370  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these
6371 
6372  /// The pattern of the pack expansion.
6373  QualType Pattern;
6374 
6375  PackExpansionType(QualType Pattern, QualType Canon,
6376  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions)
6377  : Type(PackExpansion, Canon,
6378  (Pattern->getDependence() | TypeDependence::Dependent |
6379  TypeDependence::Instantiation) &
6380  ~TypeDependence::UnexpandedPack),
6381  Pattern(Pattern) {
6382  PackExpansionTypeBits.NumExpansions =
6383  NumExpansions ? *NumExpansions + 1 : 0;
6384  }
6385 
6386 public:
6387  /// Retrieve the pattern of this pack expansion, which is the
6388  /// type that will be repeatedly instantiated when instantiating the
6389  /// pack expansion itself.
6390  QualType getPattern() const { return Pattern; }
6391 
6392  /// Retrieve the number of expansions that this pack expansion will
6393  /// generate, if known.
6394  std::optional<unsigned> getNumExpansions() const {
6395  if (PackExpansionTypeBits.NumExpansions)
6396  return PackExpansionTypeBits.NumExpansions - 1;
6397  return std::nullopt;
6398  }
6399 
6400  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6401  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6402 
6403  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
6404  Profile(ID, getPattern(), getNumExpansions());
6405  }
6406 
6407  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, QualType Pattern,
6408  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions) {
6409  ID.AddPointer(Pattern.getAsOpaquePtr());
6410  ID.AddBoolean(NumExpansions.has_value());
6411  if (NumExpansions)
6412  ID.AddInteger(*NumExpansions);
6413  }
6414 
6415  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6416  return T->getTypeClass() == PackExpansion;
6417  }
6418 };
6419 
6420 /// This class wraps the list of protocol qualifiers. For types that can
6421 /// take ObjC protocol qualifers, they can subclass this class.
6422 template <class T>
6423 class ObjCProtocolQualifiers {
6424 protected:
6425  ObjCProtocolQualifiers() = default;
6426 
6427  ObjCProtocolDecl * const *getProtocolStorage() const {
6428  return const_cast<ObjCProtocolQualifiers*>(this)->getProtocolStorage();
6429  }
6430 
6431  ObjCProtocolDecl **getProtocolStorage() {
6432  return static_cast<T*>(this)->getProtocolStorageImpl();
6433  }
6434 
6435  void setNumProtocols(unsigned N) {
6436  static_cast<T*>(this)->setNumProtocolsImpl(N);
6437  }
6438 
6439  void initialize(ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols) {
6440  setNumProtocols(protocols.size());
6441  assert(getNumProtocols() == protocols.size() &&
6442  "bitfield overflow in protocol count");
6443  if (!protocols.empty())
6444  memcpy(getProtocolStorage(), protocols.data(),
6445  protocols.size() * sizeof(ObjCProtocolDecl*));
6446  }
6447 
6448 public:
6449  using qual_iterator = ObjCProtocolDecl * const *;
6450  using qual_range = llvm::iterator_range<qual_iterator>;
6451 
6452  qual_range quals() const { return qual_range(qual_begin(), qual_end()); }
6453  qual_iterator qual_begin() const { return getProtocolStorage(); }
6454  qual_iterator qual_end() const { return qual_begin() + getNumProtocols(); }
6455 
6456  bool qual_empty() const { return getNumProtocols() == 0; }
6457 
6458  /// Return the number of qualifying protocols in this type, or 0 if
6459  /// there are none.
6460  unsigned getNumProtocols() const {
6461  return static_cast<const T*>(this)->getNumProtocolsImpl();
6462  }
6463 
6464  /// Fetch a protocol by index.
6465  ObjCProtocolDecl *getProtocol(unsigned I) const {
6466  assert(I < getNumProtocols() && "Out-of-range protocol access");
6467  return qual_begin()[I];
6468  }
6469 
6470  /// Retrieve all of the protocol qualifiers.
6471  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> getProtocols() const {
6472  return ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *>(qual_begin(), getNumProtocols());
6473  }
6474 };

6493 
6494  /// Return the number of qualifying protocols in this interface type,

6498  }
6499 
6500  void setNumProtocolsImpl(unsigned N) {

6502  }

6525 /// Represents a class type in Objective C.
6526 ///
6527 /// Every Objective C type is a combination of a base type, a set of
6528 /// type arguments (optional, for parameterized classes) and a list of
6529 /// protocols.
6530 ///
6531 /// Given the following declarations:
6532 /// \code
6533 /// \@class C<T>;
6534 /// \@protocol P;
6535 /// \endcode
6536 ///
6537 /// 'C' is an ObjCInterfaceType C. It is sugar for an ObjCObjectType
6538 /// with base C and no protocols.
6539 ///
6540 /// 'C<P>' is an unspecialized ObjCObjectType with base C and protocol list [P].
6541 /// 'C<C*>' is a specialized ObjCObjectType with type arguments 'C*' and no
6542 /// protocol list.
6543 /// 'C<C*><P>' is a specialized ObjCObjectType with base C, type arguments 'C*',
6544 /// and protocol list [P].
6545 ///
6546 /// 'id' is a TypedefType which is sugar for an ObjCObjectPointerType whose
6547 /// pointee is an ObjCObjectType with base BuiltinType::ObjCIdType
6548 /// and no protocols.
6549 ///
6550 /// 'id<P>' is an ObjCObjectPointerType whose pointee is an ObjCObjectType
6551 /// with base BuiltinType::ObjCIdType and protocol list [P]. Eventually
6552 /// this should get its own sugar class to better represent the source.
6553 class ObjCObjectType : public Type,
6554  public ObjCProtocolQualifiers<ObjCObjectType> {
6555  friend class ObjCProtocolQualifiers<ObjCObjectType>;
6556 
6557  // ObjCObjectType.NumTypeArgs - the number of type arguments stored
6558  // after the ObjCObjectPointerType node.
6559  // ObjCObjectType.NumProtocols - the number of protocols stored
6560  // after the type arguments of ObjCObjectPointerType node.
6561  //
6562  // These protocols are those written directly on the type. If
6563  // protocol qualifiers ever become additive, the iterators will need
6564  // to get kindof complicated.
6565  //
6566  // In the canonical object type, these are sorted alphabetically
6567  // and uniqued.
6568 
6569  /// Either a BuiltinType or an InterfaceType or sugar for either.
6570  QualType BaseType;
6571 
6572  /// Cached superclass type.
6573  mutable llvm::PointerIntPair<const ObjCObjectType *, 1, bool>
6574  CachedSuperClassType;
6575 
6576  QualType *getTypeArgStorage();
6577  const QualType *getTypeArgStorage() const {
6578  return const_cast<ObjCObjectType *>(this)->getTypeArgStorage();
6579  }
6580 
6581  ObjCProtocolDecl **getProtocolStorageImpl();
6582  /// Return the number of qualifying protocols in this interface type,
6583  /// or 0 if there are none.
6584  unsigned getNumProtocolsImpl() const {
6585  return ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumProtocols;
6586  }
6587  void setNumProtocolsImpl(unsigned N) {
6588  ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumProtocols = N;
6589  }
6590 
6591 protected:
6592  enum Nonce_ObjCInterface { Nonce_ObjCInterface };
6593 
6594  ObjCObjectType(QualType Canonical, QualType Base,
6595  ArrayRef<QualType> typeArgs,
6596  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols,
6597  bool isKindOf);
6598 
6599  ObjCObjectType(enum Nonce_ObjCInterface)
6600  : Type(ObjCInterface, QualType(), TypeDependence::None),
6601  BaseType(QualType(this_(), 0)) {
6602  ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumProtocols = 0;
6603  ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumTypeArgs = 0;
6604  ObjCObjectTypeBits.IsKindOf = 0;
6605  }
6606 
6607  void computeSuperClassTypeSlow() const;
6608 
6609 public:
6610  /// Gets the base type of this object type. This is always (possibly
6611  /// sugar for) one of:
6612  /// - the 'id' builtin type (as opposed to the 'id' type visible to the
6613  /// user, which is a typedef for an ObjCObjectPointerType)
6614  /// - the 'Class' builtin type (same caveat)
6615  /// - an ObjCObjectType (currently always an ObjCInterfaceType)
6616  QualType getBaseType() const { return BaseType; }
6617 
6618  bool isObjCId() const {
6619  return getBaseType()->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::ObjCId);
6620  }
6621 
6622  bool isObjCClass() const {
6623  return getBaseType()->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::ObjCClass);
6624  }
6625 
6626  bool isObjCUnqualifiedId() const { return qual_empty() && isObjCId(); }
6627  bool isObjCUnqualifiedClass() const { return qual_empty() && isObjCClass(); }
6628  bool isObjCUnqualifiedIdOrClass() const {
6629  if (!qual_empty()) return false;
6630  if (const BuiltinType *T = getBaseType()->getAs<BuiltinType>())
6631  return T->getKind() == BuiltinType::ObjCId ||
6632  T->getKind() == BuiltinType::ObjCClass;
6633  return false;
6634  }
6635  bool isObjCQualifiedId() const { return !qual_empty() && isObjCId(); }
6636  bool isObjCQualifiedClass() const { return !qual_empty() && isObjCClass(); }
6637 
6638  /// Gets the interface declaration for this object type, if the base type
6639  /// really is an interface.
6640  ObjCInterfaceDecl *getInterface() const;
6641 
6642  /// Determine whether this object type is "specialized", meaning
6643  /// that it has type arguments.
6644  bool isSpecialized() const;
6645 
6646  /// Determine whether this object type was written with type arguments.
6647  bool isSpecializedAsWritten() const {
6648  return ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumTypeArgs > 0;
6649  }
6650 
6651  /// Determine whether this object type is "unspecialized", meaning
6652  /// that it has no type arguments.
6653  bool isUnspecialized() const { return !isSpecialized(); }
6654 
6655  /// Determine whether this object type is "unspecialized" as
6656  /// written, meaning that it has no type arguments.
6657  bool isUnspecializedAsWritten() const { return !isSpecializedAsWritten(); }
6658 
6659  /// Retrieve the type arguments of this object type (semantically).
6660  ArrayRef<QualType> getTypeArgs() const;
6661 
6662  /// Retrieve the type arguments of this object type as they were
6663  /// written.
6664  ArrayRef<QualType> getTypeArgsAsWritten() const {
6665  return llvm::ArrayRef(getTypeArgStorage(), ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumTypeArgs);
6666  }
6667 
6668  /// Whether this is a "__kindof" type as written.
6669  bool isKindOfTypeAsWritten() const { return ObjCObjectTypeBits.IsKindOf; }
6670 
6671  /// Whether this ia a "__kindof" type (semantically).
6672  bool isKindOfType() const;
6673 
6674  /// Retrieve the type of the superclass of this object type.
6675  ///
6676  /// This operation substitutes any type arguments into the
6677  /// superclass of the current class type, potentially producing a
6678  /// specialization of the superclass type. Produces a null type if
6679  /// there is no superclass.
6680  QualType getSuperClassType() const {
6681  if (!CachedSuperClassType.getInt())
6682  computeSuperClassTypeSlow();
6683 
6684  assert(CachedSuperClassType.getInt() && "Superclass not set?");
6685  return QualType(CachedSuperClassType.getPointer(), 0);
6686  }
6687 
6688  /// Strip off the Objective-C "kindof" type and (with it) any
6689  /// protocol qualifiers.
6690  QualType stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(const ASTContext &ctx) const;
6691 
6692  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6693  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6694 
6695  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6696  return T->getTypeClass() == ObjCObject ||
6697  T->getTypeClass() == ObjCInterface;
6698  }
6699 };

6701 /// A class providing a concrete implementation
6702 /// of ObjCObjectType, so as to not increase the footprint of
6703 /// ObjCInterfaceType. Code outside of ASTContext and the core type

6705 class ObjCObjectTypeImpl : public ObjCObjectType, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {

6712  ArrayRef<QualType> typeArgs,
6713  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols,

6732  getTypeArgStorage() + ObjCObjectTypeBits.NumTypeArgs);

6737  static_cast<ObjCTypeParamType*>(this)+1);

6740 /// Interfaces are the core concept in Objective-C for object oriented design.
6741 /// They basically correspond to C++ classes. There are two kinds of interface
6742 /// types: normal interfaces like `NSString`, and qualified interfaces, which
6743 /// are qualified with a protocol list like `NSString<NSCopyable, NSAmazing>`.
6744 ///
6745 /// ObjCInterfaceType guarantees the following properties when considered
6746 /// as a subtype of its superclass, ObjCObjectType:
6747 /// - There are no protocol qualifiers. To reinforce this, code which
6748 /// tries to invoke the protocol methods via an ObjCInterfaceType will
6749 /// fail to compile.
6750 /// - It is its own base type. That is, if T is an ObjCInterfaceType*,
6751 /// T->getBaseType() == QualType(T, 0).
6752 class ObjCInterfaceType : public ObjCObjectType {
6753  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these.
6754  friend class ASTReader;
6755  template <class T> friend class serialization::AbstractTypeReader;
6756 
6757  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Decl;
6758 
6759  ObjCInterfaceType(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *D)
6760  : ObjCObjectType(Nonce_ObjCInterface),
6761  Decl(const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl*>(D)) {}
6762 
6763 public:
6764  /// Get the declaration of this interface.
6765  ObjCInterfaceDecl *getDecl() const;
6766 
6767  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6768  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6769 
6770  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6771  return T->getTypeClass() == ObjCInterface;
6772  }
6773 
6774  // Nonsense to "hide" certain members of ObjCObjectType within this
6775  // class. People asking for protocols on an ObjCInterfaceType are
6776  // not going to get what they want: ObjCInterfaceTypes are
6777  // guaranteed to have no protocols.
6778  enum {
6779  qual_iterator,
6780  qual_begin,
6781  qual_end,
6782  getNumProtocols,
6783  getProtocol
6784  };
6785 };
6786 
6787 inline ObjCInterfaceDecl *ObjCObjectType::getInterface() const {
6788  QualType baseType = getBaseType();
6789  while (const auto *ObjT = baseType->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()) {
6790  if (const auto *T = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(ObjT))
6791  return T->getDecl();
6792 
6793  baseType = ObjT->getBaseType();
6794  }
6795 
6796  return nullptr;
6797 }
6798 
6799 /// Represents a pointer to an Objective C object.
6800 ///
6801 /// These are constructed from pointer declarators when the pointee type is
6802 /// an ObjCObjectType (or sugar for one). In addition, the 'id' and 'Class'
6803 /// types are typedefs for these, and the protocol-qualified types 'id<P>'
6804 /// and 'Class<P>' are translated into these.
6805 ///
6806 /// Pointers to pointers to Objective C objects are still PointerTypes;
6807 /// only the first level of pointer gets it own type implementation.
6808 class ObjCObjectPointerType : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
6809  friend class ASTContext; // ASTContext creates these.
6810 
6811  QualType PointeeType;
6812 
6813  ObjCObjectPointerType(QualType Canonical, QualType Pointee)
6814  : Type(ObjCObjectPointer, Canonical, Pointee->getDependence()),
6815  PointeeType(Pointee) {}
6816 
6817 public:
6818  /// Gets the type pointed to by this ObjC pointer.
6819  /// The result will always be an ObjCObjectType or sugar thereof.
6820  QualType getPointeeType() const { return PointeeType; }
6821 
6822  /// Gets the type pointed to by this ObjC pointer. Always returns non-null.
6823  ///
6824  /// This method is equivalent to getPointeeType() except that
6825  /// it discards any typedefs (or other sugar) between this
6826  /// type and the "outermost" object type. So for:
6827  /// \code
6828  /// \@class A; \@protocol P; \@protocol Q;
6829  /// typedef A<P> AP;
6830  /// typedef A A1;
6831  /// typedef A1<P> A1P;
6832  /// typedef A1P<Q> A1PQ;
6833  /// \endcode
6834  /// For 'A*', getObjectType() will return 'A'.
6835  /// For 'A<P>*', getObjectType() will return 'A<P>'.
6836  /// For 'AP*', getObjectType() will return 'A<P>'.
6837  /// For 'A1*', getObjectType() will return 'A'.
6838  /// For 'A1<P>*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<P>'.
6839  /// For 'A1P*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<P>'.
6840  /// For 'A1PQ*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<Q>', because
6841  /// adding protocols to a protocol-qualified base discards the
6842  /// old qualifiers (for now). But if it didn't, getObjectType()
6843  /// would return 'A1P<Q>' (and we'd have to make iterating over
6844  /// qualifiers more complicated).
6845  const ObjCObjectType *getObjectType() const {
6846  return PointeeType->castAs<ObjCObjectType>();
6847  }
6848 
6849  /// If this pointer points to an Objective C
6850  /// \@interface type, gets the type for that interface. Any protocol
6851  /// qualifiers on the interface are ignored.
6852  ///
6853  /// \return null if the base type for this pointer is 'id' or 'Class'
6854  const ObjCInterfaceType *getInterfaceType() const;
6855 
6856  /// If this pointer points to an Objective \@interface
6857  /// type, gets the declaration for that interface.
6858  ///
6859  /// \return null if the base type for this pointer is 'id' or 'Class'
6860  ObjCInterfaceDecl *getInterfaceDecl() const {
6861  return getObjectType()->getInterface();
6862  }
6863 
6864  /// True if this is equivalent to the 'id' type, i.e. if
6865  /// its object type is the primitive 'id' type with no protocols.
6866  bool isObjCIdType() const {
6867  return getObjectType()->isObjCUnqualifiedId();
6868  }
6869 
6870  /// True if this is equivalent to the 'Class' type,
6871  /// i.e. if its object tive is the primitive 'Class' type with no protocols.
6872  bool isObjCClassType() const {
6873  return getObjectType()->isObjCUnqualifiedClass();
6874  }
6875 
6876  /// True if this is equivalent to the 'id' or 'Class' type,
6877  bool isObjCIdOrClassType() const {
6878  return getObjectType()->isObjCUnqualifiedIdOrClass();
6879  }
6880 
6881  /// True if this is equivalent to 'id<P>' for some non-empty set of
6882  /// protocols.
6883  bool isObjCQualifiedIdType() const {
6884  return getObjectType()->isObjCQualifiedId();
6885  }
6886 
6887  /// True if this is equivalent to 'Class<P>' for some non-empty set of
6888  /// protocols.
6889  bool isObjCQualifiedClassType() const {
6890  return getObjectType()->isObjCQualifiedClass();
6891  }
6892 
6893  /// Whether this is a "__kindof" type.
6894  bool isKindOfType() const { return getObjectType()->isKindOfType(); }
6895 
6896  /// Whether this type is specialized, meaning that it has type arguments.
6897  bool isSpecialized() const { return getObjectType()->isSpecialized(); }
6898 
6899  /// Whether this type is specialized, meaning that it has type arguments.
6900  bool isSpecializedAsWritten() const {
6901  return getObjectType()->isSpecializedAsWritten();
6902  }
6903 
6904  /// Whether this type is unspecialized, meaning that is has no type arguments.
6905  bool isUnspecialized() const { return getObjectType()->isUnspecialized(); }
6906 
6907  /// Determine whether this object type is "unspecialized" as
6908  /// written, meaning that it has no type arguments.
6909  bool isUnspecializedAsWritten() const { return !isSpecializedAsWritten(); }
6910 
6911  /// Retrieve the type arguments for this type.
6912  ArrayRef<QualType> getTypeArgs() const {
6913  return getObjectType()->getTypeArgs();
6914  }
6915 
6916  /// Retrieve the type arguments for this type.
6917  ArrayRef<QualType> getTypeArgsAsWritten() const {
6918  return getObjectType()->getTypeArgsAsWritten();
6919  }
6920 
6921  /// An iterator over the qualifiers on the object type. Provided
6922  /// for convenience. This will always iterate over the full set of
6923  /// protocols on a type, not just those provided directly.
6924  using qual_iterator = ObjCObjectType::qual_iterator;
6925  using qual_range = llvm::iterator_range<qual_iterator>;
6926 
6927  qual_range quals() const { return qual_range(qual_begin(), qual_end()); }
6928 
6929  qual_iterator qual_begin() const {
6930  return getObjectType()->qual_begin();
6931  }
6932 
6933  qual_iterator qual_end() const {
6934  return getObjectType()->qual_end();
6935  }
6936 
6937  bool qual_empty() const { return getObjectType()->qual_empty(); }
6938 
6939  /// Return the number of qualifying protocols on the object type.
6940  unsigned getNumProtocols() const {
6941  return getObjectType()->getNumProtocols();
6942  }
6943 
6944  /// Retrieve a qualifying protocol by index on the object type.
6945  ObjCProtocolDecl *getProtocol(unsigned I) const {
6946  return getObjectType()->getProtocol(I);
6947  }
6948 
6949  bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6950  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6951 
6952  /// Retrieve the type of the superclass of this object pointer type.
6953  ///
6954  /// This operation substitutes any type arguments into the
6955  /// superclass of the current class type, potentially producing a
6956  /// pointer to a specialization of the superclass type. Produces a
6957  /// null type if there is no superclass.
6958  QualType getSuperClassType() const;
6959 
6960  /// Strip off the Objective-C "kindof" type and (with it) any
6961  /// protocol qualifiers.
6962  const ObjCObjectPointerType *stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(
6963  const ASTContext &ctx) const;
6964 
6965  void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID) {
6966  Profile(ID, getPointeeType());
6967  }
6968 
6969  static void Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID, QualType T) {
6970  ID.AddPointer(T.getAsOpaquePtr());
6971  }
6972 
6973  static bool classof(const Type *T) {
6974  return T->getTypeClass() == ObjCObjectPointer;
6975  }
6976 };

7041 /// A fixed int type of a specified bitwidth.
7042 class BitIntType final : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {
7043  friend class ASTContext;

7045  unsigned IsUnsigned : 1;
7046  unsigned NumBits : 24;
7047

7049  BitIntType(bool isUnsigned, unsigned NumBits);
7050 
7051 public:

7053  bool isSigned() const { return !IsUnsigned; }
7054  unsigned getNumBits() const { return NumBits; }
7055

7057  QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
7058

7060  Profile(ID, isUnsigned(), getNumBits());
7061  }
7062

7064  unsigned NumBits) {
7065  ID.AddBoolean(IsUnsigned);
7066  ID.AddInteger(NumBits);
7067  }

7070 };

7072 class DependentBitIntType final : public Type, public llvm::FoldingSetNode {

7098 /// A qualifier set is used to build a set of qualifiers.
7099 class QualifierCollector : public Qualifiers {
7100 public:
7101  QualifierCollector(Qualifiers Qs = Qualifiers()) : Qualifiers(Qs) {}
7102 
7103  /// Collect any qualifiers on the given type and return an
7104  /// unqualified type. The qualifiers are assumed to be consistent
7105  /// with those already in the type.
7106  const Type *strip(QualType type) {
7107  addFastQualifiers(type.getLocalFastQualifiers());
7108  if (!type.hasLocalNonFastQualifiers())
7109  return type.getTypePtrUnsafe();
7110 
7111  const ExtQuals *extQuals = type.getExtQualsUnsafe();
7112  addConsistentQualifiers(extQuals->getQualifiers());
7113  return extQuals->getBaseType();
7114  }
7115 
7116  /// Apply the collected qualifiers to the given type.
7117  QualType apply(const ASTContext &Context, QualType QT) const;
7118 
7119  /// Apply the collected qualifiers to the given type.
7120  QualType apply(const ASTContext &Context, const Type* T) const;
7121 };

7123 /// A container of type source information.
7124 ///
7125 /// A client can read the relevant info using TypeLoc wrappers, e.g:
7126 /// @code
7127 /// TypeLoc TL = TypeSourceInfo->getTypeLoc();
7128 /// TL.getBeginLoc().print(OS, SrcMgr);
7129 /// @endcode
7130 class alignas(8) TypeSourceInfo {
7131  // Contains a memory block after the class, used for type source information,
7132  // allocated by ASTContext.
7133  friend class ASTContext;
7134 
7135  QualType Ty;
7136 
7137  TypeSourceInfo(QualType ty, size_t DataSize); // implemented in TypeLoc.h
7138 
7139 public:
7140  /// Return the type wrapped by this type source info.
7141  QualType getType() const { return Ty; }
7142 
7143  /// Return the TypeLoc wrapper for the type source info.
7144  TypeLoc getTypeLoc() const; // implemented in TypeLoc.h
7145 
7146  /// Override the type stored in this TypeSourceInfo. Use with caution!
7147  void overrideType(QualType T) { Ty = T; }
7148 };
